comment.text: This translation key is used to display a message indicating that a file has been moved within a file system or directory. It appears in UI elements such as notifications or confirmation dialogs, typically after a file operation has taken place. Translators should provide a phrase that conveys the action of moving a file from its original location to a new one.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English content is plural ('Files moved'), but the Italian translation uses the singular form ('File'). While technically grammatically correct in Italian, it doesn't accurately reflect the English meaning.  It implies a single file was moved.
The Romanian translation 'Fişiere au fost mutate' is a literal translation and sounds unnatural. A more natural and idiomatic translation would be 'Fișierele mutate' or 'Fișierele au fost mutate.'

The translation 'ගොනු ගෙනයාම සිදු විය' is a literal translation that doesn't quite convey the intended meaning of 'Files moved.' It implies an action 'happened' instead of simply stating files were moved.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ගොනු ඇවත්විනි (Gonu avatvini) - This is a more natural way to say 'Files moved' in Sinhala.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Датотеке су померене.' is grammatically correct but slightly awkward. A more natural and common phrasing would be 'Премештене датотеке.' or 'Датотеке премештене'. The current phrasing implies a passive voice but isn't the most idiomatic way to express the action.

The translation "Đã di chuyển các tập tin." is technically correct, but less natural than other options. "Đã di chuyển file" or "Các file đã được di chuyển" are more common and smoother-sounding in Vietnamese.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Các file đã được di chuyển.
